sql:
SELECT api_name, description, COUNT(DISTINCT api_id) AS api_count
FROM apis
GROUP BY api_name, description;

SELECT AVG(request_id) AS average_successful_request_id
FROM api_requests
WHERE status_code = 200;

SELECT COUNT(status_id) AS status_entry_count
FROM api_status
WHERE api_id = 0;

SELECT api_name 
FROM apis 
WHERE api_id = 0;

SELECT COUNT(*) > 0 AS has_made_requests
FROM api_requests
WHERE user_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
Underperforming APIs: APIs with high error rates; 
Usage statistics: request count and error count; 
Error rate: the ratio of failed requests to total requests; 
Respective rankings (percentile rank): a ranking that indicates the percentage of APIs with lower error rates.
